{"/service/ndnp/in/batch_in_fairbanks_ver01/data/sn87055779/00296021544/1920112601/0181.xml":{"full_text":"w\n20\nmm.Y MOItYTYC, NfVi:MRini 2C, 1920.\nTHE SOUTH BEND NEWS-TIMES\n1\nf\nu'\";:f\",\"T7T!!ri:iv\":.v':.r m u.\n.--n------ ----nrnr ii i r iiim i m l r--iii t J\nBUSINESS OUTLOOK\ni\nThe Most Common Thing in the World\nWhat is the most common thing in the world?\nWithout it cur existence would not be possible.\nWithout it we could not have food, clothing,\nhomes in fact, any cf the necessities cf life.\nWithout it our bodies would quickly perish.\nWhat is this thing so common, yet\nso vital in our lives? It is Water.\nThere is nothing which craves\nwater more than the human body, and\nnaturally so, for water is the body's most\nessential constituent.\nIn addition to performing other\nnecessary functions in the human body,\nwater is recognized as a most important\naid to digestion. Its value in helping the\ndigestive and climinative system to per\nform properly is well known.\nAn important health aid\nIs it not natural, then, that thou\nean'ds of well informed physicians recom\nmend the use of a water laxative when the\nsystem need3 a cleansing? Physicians\neverywhere prescribe a harmless mineral\nwater known as Pluto. This water, due to\nthe minerals it contains, completely and\ngently flushes the system of its waste\naccumulation.\nIn the rush of everyday life, we\nso often thoughtlessly neglect our bodies\nuntil wc find at last that even Nature can\nno longer function properly. We slow\ndown feel out of sorts become listless\nand inefficient in work and pleasure.\nThe condition is common in mod\nern life. You, perhaps, have felt this way\nmany times. When you find yourself in\nthis condition, what do you do? Either\nyou consult a physitian; or, if you are\nconscious of your physical neglect, com\nmon sense tells you what is wrong. You\nneed a good physic.\nFlush away the impurities\nTake Pluto Water the sensible,\nquick-acting water laxative. Pluto will\nquickly flush away the disease-breeding\nimpurities. It will restore normal, healthy\nactivity you will feel fine once more.\nPluto Water is pleasant in action cer\ntain in results. It is beneficial to children\nas well as grown-ups, and should be kept\nalways in the home for regular and emer\ngency use.\nMany people take Pluto Water\nperiodically, whether or not they are con\nstipated. They wisely avoid dangerous\nconstipation in this way. Ask your drug\ngist today for a bottle of Pluto Water.\nKeep it always handy. As a laxative take\n4 tumbler of Pluto; as a cathartic, Y$\ntumbler; as a purgative, j tumbler- add\nhot or cold water to fill glass. Bottled at\nFrench Lick Springs, Indiana.\nStacks of rr.f rchar.diso will, it is\nrriJict-l .rrx h tho lowfst point in\ny:ir by January 1. Manufacturers\nare rcstrictir: production and mcr\nhunts are slowly clrarir.c away the\njic-cumulation of hih-priccd poods\nwhich is blocking resumption of in\ndustrial activity. They are tie in;: so\nin most cases hy offering' the public\nfrenuino values at substantial re\nductions. Stocks in lirst hand.- are\nsteadily decnasinff. The buyer's\napathy will vanish, once prices reach\na fairly stable level. Renewed de\nmand may find a scarcity of poods\nIn actual fact. Firming prices will\nresult.\nKastern bankers convey a.urancc\nthat the nation's financial and in\ndustrial condition is fundamentally\nsound. Hik'h officials diredit re\nports that an abnormally largre num\nber of \"failures wil occur within the\nnext four months. A very fair vol\nume of business is In prospec t. De\nlation is painful, but wil be merci-\nfully short, judpir.p from its present\nspt-d. The period of liquidation will\nnot compare in length with the two\ncorespor.dinc periods of 1S73-M and\n1S33-LO. The Federal Re?ere sys\nI tern holds its t nuipency power in\nI reserve as a protection to industry\nj in any crisis. Price r action in pri\nj niary markets, as Dun's comments.\nlias caused less disturbance than\nI business men had reason to expect,\nland more wholesome conditions will\nfollow completion of the present\nreadjust ment.\nL. J. Replole ureres the stronger\niniifftnlj a ?n nV.lh'.'ttion to \"m.iin-\n1 aUi Vuuo t vw..r.v.--..\ntain a fair business balance\" by\nplacinp liberal orders for rails.\nRoplojrle points out that the 40 per\ncent increase in rates will produce\nvery little for the roads unless they\nin common with other business in\nterests help to rmlntain a fair vol\nume of trade. The time is coming\nwhen lare consumers may well\nplao their orders at fair prices for\nthe sake of tiding over other con\ncerns and individuals who in turn\nconsume their product.\nf\nj cau.in? a sharp rally. Corn and\nj oats touched new low points for th\nj season. Later markets saw a con\ntinuation of the downward trti.,1\nwith intermittent support.\nn\nSouth Bend Markets\ni\ndo not worry the Investor\nwho buys bach prade listed\nstocks and bonds outright\nand holds them for perma\nnent profit.\nThe Krictxt Plan of tright bor\ning on convenient payments will\nnuke of you a good Investor. It\nenables you to control five times as\nlarte m block of securities as vou\ncould rcrtol on a cash basis. You\nget ail dividends hile paring.\nOur magazine. \"Investment,\" will\nkeep you posted on the vital news\nabout the better clans of listed securi\nties. Ask us to snd it to you free\nfor sbx months. Dept. 1.\nYour physician prescribes it\nSTOCKS.\nX,-. market touched new low lev\nels for the v-'-r on Monday, due to\nthe Kloom cast by peneral industrial\ncondition?. An undertone of strength\nwas manifest the next day. Stocks\nbroke under heavy selling Wednes\nday, then rallied silently. Thurs\nday's million-share market was de\npressed, liquidation forcing prices\ndownward to new low levels. Call\nmoney was quoted as low as six per\ncent. Friday's active session broucht\nstill lower prices, notwithstanding\neasy call money.\nC.RAIX.\n\"Wheat swuns upward, followed\npartially by corn and oats, in view\nof the export business, the farmers\ncontinued holding movement, Rus\nsian success in the Crimea, and the\napproaching end of lake navigation.\nTraders recognize that prices have\nsuffered very severe declines. The\nstock of wheat at western terminal\ncenters Is comparatively light. Ca\nnadian competition helped to break\nthe market Wednesday, although a\nrise in Sterling was instrumental in\nHAY. STIIA1V AND ITFD.\n(Corrected Daily by th Hslv M.ler\nFlour Feed Co.. 110 S. .Michigan.)\nNi:V HAV-i'ajiniT $22 to 12Z. telllr.g\n\"'oil' CORN raying I0-? f?ung Sl.lZ\nto fl.'o.\nSTRAW raying selling\nor s- bal.\nOATS Paying fplllr.g 70c to Sfr\nCLOVKK JsKUD-Pajing I10.CO. teVAui\n512 to $14.\nAl.SIKi: CL.OVEH Sclllrff Jll tn $H5.\nALFALFA (Northern grown) $lt3.\nGRAIN AND FUD.\ntCarrected Ialljr by Ts. n. Morrnn, Star\nXllU. Hidraultr At.)\nCORN I'ayius tn:shfl.\nOA I S-la1rg ii\"-, \u00fcfllln- 70 to S\"\nHit A N Killing 12 23.\nMIDOLINC.S SsMinsr f 2 73 hundred\nciioi'run fi;i:d-soiling :a) ,,..r\ncwt.\nSCRATCH Fi:i:i -Selling 3. 00',\nrwv.\nORINni.MJS- brshH.\nWin:AT P;iTir:ir M0.\nUVi: Pavin- si.:;..\nr.rcivWHF.Ai i a-ire $l.Z0 bunll.\nOLD CORN Faring t).\n8LKDS.\n(Carreeted Dally by tTarur Oros.\nStore. T?1 S. Mlrhlen t.)\nCOW PEAS $2.30 to $4 00 bushel.\nALFALFA $14 to $1; per bushel.\nRFI) ANI .MAMMOTH CLOi;K-1\nto 12 bushel\nAI.SIKi: $12 til hush.!.\nSFNFLoWFRS -l\u00f6 pouni\nWINTER OR II AIRY liETCH 120 00\ntundre.l pounds.\nHUT: GRASS imnhel.\nswkut wiuri: clovkr\nRFI) TOr-$4lH per bushel.\nWHITE CI.OVER-1 15.00 bu.\nFIELD PEAS f.'l. x to J4.U0 buahfl.\nRARE EED (Dwarf Es?ex) fS.OO per\nbushel.\nIAWN RASS ?32 per cwt.\nSOJA REANS (1 to San)-4400 per\nbURhei.\nCLOVER SEED to 12 bushel.\nM\nW iff J\nm 1\nUnion Tnut Company\nCaf Jpcit Boim yrlih rpeciAl\nfkvcCltS tax Gi prlracj or cua\ntomTsV\nJ. SCHULMAN CO.\nCOAL\nLincoln 5637\nCLOSING OUT SALE\nFarm Machinery\nStoves Seeds Furnaces\nAt Big Discounts\nWARNER BROS.,\n226 S. Michigan St.\nTry NEI